The duo sing the influence and carefree party-centric lifestyle afforded to pop stars. A particular emphasis is placed on the wealth afforded to pop stars by mention of luxury clothing brands and high-end cars.

annotations:
She’s a little bitch, she’s my mini-me, wannabe
 Pull up to the party, bet your boo wanna leave with me
 I got lots of friends, and they all wanna die for me
 Even enemies wanna get a co-sign from me
 She’s a little bitch, she’s my mini-me, wannabe
 Pull up to the party, bet your boo wanna leave with me
 I must be a cake, ’cause they all want a slice of me

A “cherub” is a winged creature said to attend to God in Abrahamic religions. Despite this potentially powerful position, cherubs are in fact known for being smaller than normal humans, are seen as low-ranked in some traditions, and essentially only exist to promote a more powerful figure – God.

Clair Clair compares everyone in her life to cherubs – they’re smaller, so literally “little bitches” – and ultimately, none of their actions are significant unless they involve promoting Clair Clair.
I’mma Jordin Sparks you, that’s right, no air

“No Air” was the second single from Jordin Sparks' debut album, the self-titled Jordin Sparks, and also her biggest hit to date. By saying she’s going to “Jordin Sparks” someone, Coco infers she’s going to choke someone out – because they’ll have “no air” afterwards.
Higher than a jet, even clouds wanna copy me

Clair Clair uses the word “high” as a double entendre, both referring to the altitude of a jet (about 36,000 feet) and high on drugs.

It makes sense that the clouds want to be high like her – considering most clouds are only around ~10,000 feet off the ground, Clair Clair would be much higher.

Fuck the NRA, but I’ll blow your fucking house out
 With a gun, baby, I don’t give a fuck, your lights out

This verse originated from an Instagram live in February 2021, which is now archived on their page. In this clip, Coco freestyled over a beat with guns firing.

“NRA” refers to the National Rifle Association, a pro-gun organization in the United States. Recently, the NRA has been involved in much controversy due to their open support and even political manipulation to achieve increased gun availability; this is despite unprecedented repeated numbers of mass shootings in the US. Coco says “Fuck the NRA” to openly oppose the organization.

annotations: Keke
Kiki is a term which grew out BIPOQ+ ballroom culture.
Wishy washy

Defined by the Merriam-Webster dictionary, “wishy-washy” means “lacking in character or determination”, or ineffectual. In other words, every time Clair Clair repeats this term she is referring to the man who is simping for her and how his simping is accomplishing nothing for him.
I take a lil’ off the top, he my dog, Iggy Pop

James Newell Osterberg Jr. is an American musician, singer, songwriter, record producer, and actor. In April 1969, he and The Stooges, a band he founded, released a song called “I Just Wanna Be Your Dog” as part of their self-titled debut album.



UPDATE: spacebandito420 suggested that Iggy Pop could be the New Yorker Boston terrier from the manga, anime, and OVA, ‘JoJo’s Bizarre Adventure’, that travels with the protagonists on their final expedition to Cairo, Egypt, to defeat the main antagonist, DIO.
We goin’ to the mall, I’m gettin’ Nike Shox
I am literally balls-to-the-wall insane
The term “balls-to-the-wall” means to use maximum power, which in this case means she’s insane to the max, and that’s okay.
No, I’m not Baroque but he treats me like he’s Bach

I dont' know much music vocabulary at all yet but I think this is kind of that one thing where the person means two things at once. Johann Sebastian Bach was someone who contributed a great deal to the arts of the Baroque period as a composer, and made a fair living off of it.



In the song, as she says “baroque” Coco sounds as though she is saying the word “broke”, as in poor, so if Coco is comparing this man to Bach and telling us he treats her like she’s “Baroque”, she is on one hand saying he contributes a lot to her life even though she doesn’t think of herself as special, while on the other hand she could be saying he treats her as though she doesn’t have any money to spend for herself, even though she would be financially fine without him. To put it shortly, either the he’s a really helpful guy, or a complete simp.
